## Task

Validate Verse code against digest to detect hallucinated API names.

## Problem

AI assistants frequently hallucinate Verse API names:
- Wrong method names
- Incorrect signatures
- Non-existent events

## Solution

Parse Verse code and cross-reference every symbol against digest index.

## Implementation

```rust
pub struct VerseValidator {
    digest: DigestIndex,
}

impl VerseValidator {
    pub fn validate(&self, code: &str) -> Vec<ValidationIssue> {
        let mut issues = vec![];

        // Extract symbols from code
        let symbols = self.extract_symbols(code);

        for symbol in symbols {
            match symbol.kind {
                SymbolKind::MethodCall { device, method } => {
                    if !self.digest.has_method(&device, &method) {
                        issues.push(ValidationIssue {
                            severity: Severity::Error,
                            message: format!("Unknown method: {}.{}", device, method),
                            suggestion: self.find_similar_method(&device, &method),
                        });
                    }
                }
                SymbolKind::EventSubscribe { device, event } => {
                    if !self.digest.has_event(&device, &event) {
                        issues.push(ValidationIssue {
                            severity: Severity::Error,
                            message: format!("Unknown event: {}.{}", device, event),
                            suggestion: self.find_similar_event(&device, &event),
                        });
                    }
                }
                _ => {}
            }
        }

        issues
    }

    fn find_similar_method(&self, device: &str, method: &str) -> Option<String> {
        // Levenshtein distance or fuzzy matching
        self.digest.get_device(device)?
            .methods.iter()
            .map(|m| (m, levenshtein(&m.name, method)))
            .filter(|(_, dist)| *dist < 3)
            .min_by_key(|(_, dist)| *dist)
            .map(|(m, _)| m.name.clone())
    }
}
```

